"{\n  \"text\": \"I've been selling fermented foods at the farmers markets for about five years, and in this five years, I've met a lot of people who were very, very sick with gut disorders. And a lot of times they were thin, they were pale, they were wasting away, and they were scared because they the doctors uh couldn't do anything for them. They gave them antibiotics which in the short term made them better, in the long term it made them worse. This was something that was is was defying them, and they had read all about fermented foods and they were coming to me to try this out. And a lot of times these people could trace back the their problems to a hardcore regimen of serious antibiotics for a serious infection, for instance, MERSA or something like this, where the antibiotics saved their life, but there was a price to be paid, and that was with the health of the gut bacteria. This is something that you need to take the antibiotics when it's going to prevent infection and help peel infection, but you also need to work against them to counter the damage that they will do to your healthy bacteria that circulates throughout your body. Thanks, y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" I've been selling fermented foods at the farmers markets for about five years, and in this five years, I've met a lot of people who were very, very sick with gut disorders.\",\n      \"start\": 0.24,\n      \"end\": 8.88,\n      \"duration\": 8.64,\n      \"confidence\": 0.992,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" I\",\n          \"start\": 0.24,\n          \"end\": 0.32,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.998\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"'\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.4,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.987\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ve\",\n          \"start\": 0.4,\n          \"end\": 0.56,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confi